";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"https://visualcomposer.com/?p=32636\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:468:\"<p>Learn how to create a WordPress child theme, get prepared codes for the style.css file and functions.php. Additionally, you can download a ready-made child theme example for the Visual Composer Starter theme.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/create-wordpress-child-theme/\">How to Create a WordPress Child Theme</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com\">Visual Composer Website Builder</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Linda R\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10709:\"<div class=\"vce-row-container\" data-vce-boxed-width=\"true\"><div class=\"vce-row vce-row--col-gap-30 vce-row-equal-height vce-row-content--top\" id=\"el-40035787\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-40035787\"><div class=\"vce-row-content\" data-vce-element-content=\"true\"><div class=\"vce-col vce-col--md-auto vce-col--xs-1 vce-col--xs-last vce-col--xs-first vce-col--sm-last vce-col--sm-first vce-col--md-last vce-col--lg-last vce-col--xl-last vce-col--md-first vce-col--lg-first vce-col--xl-first\" id=\"el-8357d5df\"><div class=\"vce-col-inner\" data-vce-do-apply=\"border margin background  el-8357d5df\"><div class=\"vce-col-content\" data-vce-element-content=\"true\" data-vce-do-apply=\"padding el-8357d5df\"><div class=\"vce-text-block\"><div class=\"vce-text-block-wrapper vce\" id=\"el-a061276d\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-a061276d\"><p><strong>Here you will learn how to create a WordPress child theme. You will have prepared codes for the <em>style.css</em> file and <em>functions.php</em>, all you have to do is copy / paste them. Additionally, you can download a ready-made child theme example for the Visual Composer Starter theme. </strong></p><p>Ready to jump in?&nbsp; Let\'s go! <span id=\"emoji-info-value\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/1f916.png\" alt=\"?\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></span></p><p>One of the greatest benefits to using WordPress is that you can take advantage of a large number of ready-made themes, all of which are customizable by users with ease. However, this customizability comes at the cost of maintenance in case your customization project isn\'t compatible when an update happens on your chosen theme.</p><p>So, if you\'re a WordPress user, it\'s best to create child themes on each of your sites. This is the only way that you can avoid losing all of your hard work if an update overwrites customizations made in the original theme files.</p><h2>What Is A Child Theme</h2><p>A WordPress child theme is a separate style sheet that changes the look of your parent\'s themes styling and adds extra functionality to a WordPress website.</p><p>Firstly, it allows developers and designers to modify the design of a website with minimum disruption. If you want one part of your site in red but most other parts blue, then creating a separate child theme for each section would be far less disruptive than modifying every page on the site (<em>which could break things</em>).</p><p>Secondly - and more importantly from a technical standpoint - child themes existence means that it is possible to update an entire WordPress installation without ever touching any core files or data stored within them.</p><h2>Benefits Of A Child Theme</h2><p>There are many benefits to creating a child theme for your WordPress site. A parent theme is pre-built and already functional, so you can make some great modifications without wrecking the original functionality of it or requiring extensive development on your end.</p><p>Some of these include:</p><ul><li>Making sure that customizations will be portable and replicable;</li><li>Keeping customization separate from functions in the main files (<em>this allows updates to affect only those parts</em>);</li><li>Allowing parents themes to receive bug fixes by overwriting CSS/themes rather than reworking all changes;</li><li>Saving time as you\'re not recreating something which has been tested beforehand - this also means learning new skills rather than relying on old ones if they no longer apply correctly.</li></ul><h2>How to Create A WordPress Child Theme</h2><p>In this tutorial, I will be using the <a href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/visual-composer-starter-theme/\">Visual Composer Starter theme</a>. Here you can download a free child theme example for the Starter theme - <a href=\"https://github.com/VisualComposer/visual-composer-starter-child\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">child theme zip file</a>.</p><p><a href=\"https://github.com/VisualComposer/visual-composer-starter-child\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-32643 size-full\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/visual-composer-starter-child.png\" alt=\"Visual Composer Starter Child Theme\" width=\"1013\" height=\"467\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/visual-composer-starter-child.png 1013w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/visual-composer-starter-child-300x138.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/visual-composer-starter-child-768x354.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/visual-composer-starter-child-848x391.png 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1013px) 100vw, 1013px\" /></a></p><p>For those who want to go through the process, let\'s keep on going further and make a new directory in the theme folder. Use either the cPanel or upload your file via FTP. The themes directory can be found in wp-content/themes.</p><h3>Create a Child Theme Folder</h3><p>To create a child theme folder, first, open your file manager and navigate to the wp-content/themes directory. Once you are there, create a new folder. Name the child theme whatever you want, but something clear and easy would be great. I recommend using <em>themename-child</em>.</p><h3>Create a stylesheet: style.css</h3><p>In your child theme folder create <strong>style.css</strong> file and add a stylesheet header to the file (if you\'re using a Stater theme, simply copy/paste).</p><pre class=\"EnlighterJSRAW\" data-enlighter-language=\"generic\">/* \nTheme Name: Visual Composer Starter Child Theme \nURI: https://visualcomposer.com \nDescription: Visual Composer Starter child theme \nAuthor: The Visual Composer Team Author \nURI: https://visualcomposer.com \nTemplate: visual-composer-starter \nVersion: 1.0.0 License: GNU General Public License v2 or later License \nURI: http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.html \nTags: light, blog, starter, responsive-layout, accessibility-ready, sandwich-menu \nText Domain: visual-composer-starter-child\n*/</pre></div></div><div class=\"vce-text-block\"><div class=\"vce-text-block-wrapper vce\" id=\"el-b64c0dd6\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-b64c0dd6\"><p>Now you should create functions.php and add the following code:</p><pre class=\"EnlighterJSRAW\" data-enlighter-language=\"generic\">add_action( ‘wp_enqueue_scripts’, ‘enqueue_parent_styles’ ); \n\nfunction enqueue_parent_styles() { \nwp_enqueue_style( ‘parent-style’, get_template_directory_uri().’/style.css’ );</pre><p>&nbsp;</p></div></div><div class=\"vce-text-block\"><div class=\"vce-text-block-wrapper vce\" id=\"el-c5bd89ae\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-c5bd89ae\"><p><strong>Note</strong>: If you want to create a custom cover image for your theme - create image 1200×900 pixels, name it <em>screenshot.png</em> and upload it to your child theme folder.</p><p><span id=\"emoji-info-value\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/1f4a1.png\" alt=\"?\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></span>&nbsp;If you would like to learn more about CSS, here is a nice post on <a href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/wordpress-css-styles/\">how to modify WordPress CSS styles</a> - with a video tutorial!</p><p>Now it\'s time to ​​install and activate the child theme.</p><h3>Install + Activate The Child Theme</h3><p>To install the child theme, you can either upload it via FTP or create a zip file of that folder and then click on <strong>Appearance</strong> - <strong>Themes</strong> - <strong>Add New</strong> in order to import to WordPress. After the installation, the last step is to activate the child theme.</p><h2>Style.css Values</h2><p>It is important to add proper values to your child theme style.css to work properly.</p><ul><li>Theme Name: The name of the theme that will appear in your WordPress;</li><li>Theme URI: A URL to the theme demonstration which is required if you wish to push your theme to the WordPress theme repository;</li><li>Description: Theme description that will appear in your WordPress by clicking on the Theme Details option;</li><li>Author: The author of the theme – you;</li><li>Author URI: Author website address;</li><li>Template: The most important part – is the place where you need to specify the name of the parent theme folder. This is case-sensitive and needs to be 100% correct in order to function as a child theme;</li><li>Version: A version of your child theme that is suggested to start with 1.0;</li><li>License: Specify the license of your child theme. Make sure that your license is the same as your parent theme license;</li><li>License URI: Link to the license explanation, again you should follow your parent theme licensing;</li><li>Tags: Tags that are relevant to your child’s theme;</li><li>Text domain: Used to make your theme translatable and should fit the ‘slug’ of your theme.</li></ul><p>And remember, if the lines of code seem complicated to you, here you can <a href=\"https://github.com/VisualComposer/visual-composer-starter-child\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">download a free child theme example for the Starter theme</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"vce-row-container\" data-vce-boxed-width=\"true\"><div class=\"vce-row vce-row--col-gap-30 vce-row-equal-height vce-row-content--top\" id=\"el-727dbf4f\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-727dbf4f\"><div class=\"vce-row-content\" data-vce-element-content=\"true\"><div class=\"vce-col vce-col--md-auto vce-col--xs-1 vce-col--xs-last vce-col--xs-first vce-col--sm-last vce-col--sm-first vce-col--md-last vce-col--lg-last vce-col--xl-last vce-col--md-first vce-col--lg-first vce-col--xl-first\" id=\"el-f9e2e98d\"><div class=\"vce-col-inner\" data-vce-do-apply=\"border margin background  el-f9e2e98d\"><div class=\"vce-col-content\" data-vce-element-content=\"true\" data-vce-do-apply=\"padding el-f9e2e98d\"><div class=\"vce-button--style-basic-container vce-button--style-basic-container--align-center\"><span class=\"vce-button--style-basic-wrapper vce\" id=\"el-8d0b729f\" data-vce-do-apply=\"margin el-8d0b729f\"><a class=\"vce-button--style-basic vce-button--style-basic--border-square vce-button--style-basic--size-medium vce-button--style-basic--color-b-255-174-39--fff vce-button--style-basic--hover-color-b-27-71-160--fff\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/visual-composer-starter-theme/\" title=\"\" data-vce-do-apply=\"padding border background  el-8d0b729f\">Download Visual Composer Starter Theme</a></span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/create-wordpress-child-theme/\">How to Create a WordPress Child Theme</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com\">Visual Composer Website Builder</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/create-wordpress-child-theme/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"How to Install WordPress (3 Simple Ways)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/how-to-install-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/how-to-install-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 07 Sep 2021 08:00:07 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"https://visualcomposer.com/?p=32600\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:397:\"<p>WordPress is famous for its 5 minutes installation. This tutorial explains how to install WordPress through hosting, locally and manually.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/how-to-install-wordpress/\">How to Install WordPress (3 Simple Ways)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com\">Visual Composer Website Builder</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Nikola Puciriusa\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21286:\"<div class=\"vce-row-container\" data-vce-boxed-width=\"true\"><div class=\"vce-row vce-row--col-gap-30 vce-row-equal-height vce-row-content--top\" id=\"el-8241ee99\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-8241ee99\"><div class=\"vce-row-content\" data-vce-element-content=\"true\"><div class=\"vce-col vce-col--md-auto vce-col--xs-1 vce-col--xs-last vce-col--xs-first vce-col--sm-last vce-col--sm-first vce-col--md-last vce-col--lg-last vce-col--xl-last vce-col--md-first vce-col--lg-first vce-col--xl-first\" id=\"el-1336ef4f\"><div class=\"vce-col-inner\" data-vce-do-apply=\"border margin background  el-1336ef4f\"><div class=\"vce-col-content\" data-vce-element-content=\"true\" data-vce-do-apply=\"padding el-1336ef4f\"><div class=\"vce-text-block\"><div class=\"vce-text-block-wrapper vce\" id=\"el-39df4979\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-39df4979\"><p>WordPress is the most popular CMS (content management system) in the world, powering over 42% of all websites on the internet. This is due to a flexible learning process (also well known for the<strong> 5-minute installation</strong>), limitless creation and customization possibilities, and a powerful community behind it.</p><p>WordPress.org is a self-hosted, open-source platform that is <strong>free</strong> for anyone to use. The main difference from WordPress.com is that you need a <strong>domain</strong>, a <strong>hosting</strong> provider and meet certain <strong>technical requirements.</strong></p><p>In this article, we explain how to install WordPress in three ways - through a hosting provider <strong>(easiest way)</strong>, locally by hosting your website on your own computer, and manually using FTP (data transfer system).</p><p>Note that the manual installation requires a bit more technical knowledge, but is doable if you stick to the instructions. We would recommend using the hosting approach because it\'s the most convenient way. Hence, you need hosting, either way, so shoot two rabbits with one shot!</p><h2>Requirements prior to the installation</h2><p>Before installation, make sure that your hosting provider meets these <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/about/requirements/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WordPress requirements</a>:</p><ul><li>PHP version 7.4 or greater.</li><li>MySQL version 5.6 or greater OR</li><li>MariaDB version 10.1 or greater.</li><li>HTTPS support</li></ul><p>And <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/article/before-you-install/#requirements-on-local\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">requirements for local installation</a>:</p><ul><li>Login Account (user id and password) to the server via FTP or shell</li><li>Text Editor</li><li>FTP</li><li>Your web browser of choice</li></ul><p>WordPress recommends using <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">these</a> hostings, but nevertheless, most of the top hosting providers offer <strong>one-click</strong> WordPress installations, due to the popularity of the platform.</p><p>We recommend using <strong>Cloudways</strong> (managed cloud hosting) since it has user-friendly hosting plans (plus a free trial), a fast setup, and provides excellent uptime. Meaning users get an overall better performance, security, and top-notch support.</p><h2>1st way: Auto-install WordPress via hosting (Cloudways)</h2><p><strong>Estimated time for installation:</strong> 10 minutes</p><ol><li>Create a free account on <a href=\"https://www.cloudways.com/en/visual-composer-partnership.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cloudways</a>;</li><li>After verifying your account, start by launching your free trial server;<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-32606 size-large\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-wordpress-installation-1024x436.png\" alt=\"Cloudways Managed Cloud Hosting for WordPress Installation\" width=\"848\" height=\"361\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-wordpress-installation-1024x436.png 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-wordpress-installation-300x128.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-wordpress-installation-768x327.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-wordpress-installation-848x361.png 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-wordpress-installation-1140x485.png 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-wordpress-installation-1170x498.png 1170w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-wordpress-installation.png 1340w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 848px\" /></li><li>Choose the WordPress version that fits your needs - we recommend choosing the first option, which is also optimized for Cloudways;</li><li>Enter a name for your application, server, and project (completely up to you);</li><li>Configure server settings - choose a provider (DigitalOcean - in our example) and server size for your website (which you can always upgrade);</li><li>And finally, select your server location (take your target audience\'s location into consideration for the best choice);<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-32604 size-large\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-installation-1024x648.png\" alt=\"Cloudways Managed Cloud Hosting Server Setup and configuration\" width=\"848\" height=\"537\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-installation-1024x648.png 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-installation-300x190.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-installation-768x486.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-installation-848x536.png 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-installation-1140x721.png 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-installation-1170x740.png 1170w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-installation.png 1360w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 848px\" /></li><li>Now your website is live, to access it, click on the orange dot on the right-hand side and select the application (from the previous step);<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-32601 size-large\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-access-website-1024x371.png\" alt=\"Cloudways Managed Cloud Hosting application access\" width=\"848\" height=\"307\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-access-website-1024x371.png 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-access-website-300x109.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-access-website-768x278.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-access-website-848x307.png 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-access-website-1140x413.png 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-access-website-1170x423.png 1170w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-access-website.png 1340w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 848px\" /></li><li>Click on the website link provided on the application management page (under the admin panel) to open your website;</li><li>To access your WordPress dashboard, add /wp-admin at the end of your website URL, copy and paste the username and password from the Cloudways admin panel. And you\'re done!<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-32605 size-large\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-website-settings-1024x512.png\" alt=\"Cloudways Managed Cloud Hosting Admin Panel settings\" width=\"848\" height=\"424\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-website-settings-1024x512.png 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-website-settings-300x150.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-website-settings-768x384.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-website-settings-848x424.png 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-website-settings-1140x570.png 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-website-settings-1170x585.png 1170w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-website-settings.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 848px\" /></li></ol><p>Lastly, before you start building your website, get a suitable domain name - <a href=\"https://domains.google/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">domains.google</a> &amp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.domain.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">domain.com</a> are a couple of great domain providers (starting as low as $7/yr).</p><p>In theory, you can live without a domain and use your IP address to access the site or use the randomly generated domain your hosting service provides. But, it is a common practice to use a domain that represents your brand, so don\'t sleep on it!</p><p>After you\'ve purchased your domain, you can change it in the Cloudways settings under \'Domain Management\'.<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-32602 size-large\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-domain-managment-1024x418.png\" alt=\"Cloudways Managed Cloud Hosting domain management settings\" width=\"848\" height=\"346\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-domain-managment-1024x418.png 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-domain-managment-300x123.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-domain-managment-768x314.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-domain-managment-848x346.png 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-domain-managment-1140x466.png 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-domain-managment-1170x478.png 1170w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/cloudways-domain-managment.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 848px\" /></p><p>Note that Cloudways also offers a free SSL certificate <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/1f512.png\" alt=\"?\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" />&nbsp; (with <a href=\"https://letsencrypt.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Let\'s Encrypt</a>), which is crucial for visitors to know that your site is secure, which is yet another reason to choose Cloudways hosting.</p><h2>2nd way: Install WordPress locally (LocalWP)</h2><p><strong>Estimated time for installation:</strong> 5 minutes</p><p><a href=\"https://localwp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">LocalWP</a> is a testing environment that lets you host your website on your own computer. This is a great way for designers and developers to create a website (for themselves or clients) to later on transfer to the live site.</p><p><strong>MAMP</strong> and <strong>XAMPP</strong> are also popular local servers, and you can learn more about the benefits of each of the servers <a href=\"https://deliciousbrains.com/xampp-mamp-local-dev/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a>.</p><ol><li>Download Local to get the .zip file;</li><li>Install the application on your computer;</li><li>Once you\'ve opened the application, click on \'Create a new site\' and enter a name for your site;<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-32609\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-set-up.png\" alt=\"LocalWP Hosting website name set up\" width=\"900\" height=\"561\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-set-up.png 995w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-set-up-300x187.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-set-up-768x479.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-set-up-848x528.png 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></li><li>Now, pick an environment for your website, you can select either \'Preferred\' (as in our case) or \'Custom\' if you wish to select a different PHP version, web server, or database;<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-32607\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-enviorment.png\" alt=\"LocalWP Hosting website environment set up\" width=\"900\" height=\"564\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-enviorment.png 990w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-enviorment-300x188.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-enviorment-768x481.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-enviorment-848x531.png 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></li><li>Next up, set up your WordPress username, password, and email;<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-32610\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-user-data.png\" alt=\"LocalWP Hosting user date set up\" width=\"900\" height=\"564\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-user-data.png 990w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-user-data-300x188.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-user-data-768x481.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-user-data-848x531.png 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></li><li>Once the download is complete, you can start creating a website from scratch locally (for your eyes only) and access it by clicking on the \'Admin\' to log in to your WordPress Admin Panel (with the credentials you created in the previous step) or \'Open Site\' to view your site.<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-32608\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-ready.png\" alt=\"LocalWP Hosting finished set up\" width=\"900\" height=\"582\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-ready.png 990w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-ready-300x194.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-ready-768x496.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/local-host-ready-848x548.png 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></li></ol><h2>3rd way: Install WordPress manually using FTP (MySQL)</h2><p><strong>Estimated time for installation:</strong> 12 minutes</p><p>This tutorial will explain to you how to install WordPress on your existing web server (live or local) with <strong>MySQL</strong>, but you can also use <strong>MariaDB.</strong></p><ol><li>Download the latest version of <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/download/#download-install\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WordPress.org</a> to get the zip file;<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-405\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/wordpress-org-wordpress-download.png\" alt=\"Download WordPress from wordpress.org website\" width=\"840\" height=\"460\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/wordpress-org-wordpress-download.png 840w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/wordpress-org-wordpress-download-600x329.png 600w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/wordpress-org-wordpress-download-300x164.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/wordpress-org-wordpress-download-768x421.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></li><li>Create a database for WordPress on the web server. You can use the phpMyAdmin database management system which is installed on most of the web servers (how you access the database depends on your hosting provider);</li><li>In phpMyAdmin, check the section Databases and choose Create database;<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-415\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/create-wordpress-database-user.png\" alt=\"Create WordPress database user via phpMyAdmin\" width=\"855\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/create-wordpress-database-user.png 855w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/create-wordpress-database-user-600x246.png 600w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/create-wordpress-database-user-300x123.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/create-wordpress-database-user-768x314.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 855px) 100vw, 855px\" /></li></ol><p>Now you are ready to start the actual installation process:</p><ol><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Extract the zip file with WordPress installation and copy by using FTP into the root folder of your website;</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Copy wp-config-sample.php file and rename it into wp-config.php (It is always a good idea to have a blank backup copy);</li><li>Open wp-config.php file with a text editor and change the following parameters:<ul><li>\'database_name_here’‘username_here’</li><li>‘username_here’‘password_here’</li><li>‘password_here’‘localhost’</li><li>‘localhost’ – replace it with the name of your site or leave it as localhost if you plan to have WordPress locally</li></ul></li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Save the wp-config.php file (if you made changes locally you may want to upload this file to your web server to overwrite old settings).</li></ol><p>Example of wp-config.php file content:</p><pre>&lt;?php\n/**\n * The base configuration for WordPress\n *\n * The wp-config.php creation script uses this file during the\n * installation. You don\'t have to use the web site, you can\n * copy this file to \"wp-config.php\" and fill in the values.\n *\n * This file contains the following configurations:\n *\n * * MySQL settings\n * * Secret keys\n * * Database table prefix\n * * ABSPATH\n *\n * @link https://codex.wordpress.org/Editing_wp-config.php\n *\n * @package WordPress\n */\n\n// ** MySQL settings - You can get this info from your web host ** //\n/** The name of the database for WordPress */\ndefine(\'DB_NAME\', \'database_name_here\');\n\n/** MySQL database username */\ndefine(\'DB_USER\', \'username_here\');\n\n/** MySQL database password */\ndefine(\'DB_PASSWORD\', \'password_here\');\n\n/** MySQL hostname */\ndefine(\'DB_HOST\', \'localhost\');\n\n/** Database Charset to use in creating database tables. */\ndefine(\'DB_CHARSET\', \'utf8\');\n\n/** The Database Collate type. Don\'t change this if in doubt. */\ndefine(\'DB_COLLATE\', \'\');</pre><p>Now it is time to launch WordPress installation:</p><ol><li>Open your browser and enter the address http://yoursitename.com/wp-admin/install.php;<br>Run through the installation process by specifying details like site name, username, and password.</li><li>Congratulations! You have successfully installed your WordPress website. You can now login into your site via http://yoursitename.com/wp-admin/</li></ol><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-22529\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wp-login.png\" alt=\"WordPress Login: User name and password\" width=\"750\" height=\"502\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wp-login.png 750w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wp-login-300x201.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wp-login-600x402.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></p><h2>Conclusions</h2><p>We are happy to see you at the start of your WordPress journey. Once you\'ve successfully finished installing WordPress, you can follow our next tutorials:</p><ul><li><a href=\"help/wordpress-tutorials/create-child-theme/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to create a child theme</a></li><li><a href=\"help/wordpress-tutorials/customize-wordpress-theme/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to customize WordPress theme</a></li></ul><p>And, don\'t forget to get <strong>Visual Composer</strong> to make the experience even better! It\'s intuitive and has a variety of different content elements, pre-made templates &amp; addons that help create beautiful websites in the fastest way possible <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/2b07.png\" alt=\"⬇\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0px;\">&nbsp;</span></p></div></div><div class=\"vce-button--style-basic-container vce-button--style-basic-container--align-center\"><span class=\"vce-button--style-basic-wrapper vce\" id=\"el-fc141e05\" data-vce-do-apply=\"margin el-fc141e05\"><a class=\"vce-button--style-basic vce-button--style-basic--border-square vce-button--style-basic--size-medium vce-button--style-basic--color-b-255-174-39--fff vce-button--style-basic--hover-color-b-27-71-160--fff\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/download/\" title=\"\" data-vce-do-apply=\"padding border background  el-fc141e05\">Download a Free Website Builder</a></span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/how-to-install-wordpress/\">How to Install WordPress (3 Simple Ways)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com\">Visual Composer Website Builder</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/how-to-install-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s: